data.description: Covers the most current knowledge of the principles of development and organogenesis with a particular focus on novel experimental and analytical approaches (microscopy, single cell multi-omics, bioinformatics). Focuses on the molecular and cellular pathways leading to normal tissue and organ development and regeneration, including in depth discussions of specification and differentiation processes.
